    • Method Detail

      • beforeEverything

        OperationResult beforeEverything(BDDObject notAMatchTarget,
                                 List<BDDObject> recordsToUnmatch)
        Called before the Mark Not A Match operation is started. Can perform data verification and return code that will stop the Mark Not A Match operation with an error. This type of operation supports the following return codes:
        • OperationExecutionErrorType.ERROR
        • OperationExecutionErrorType.WARNING
        • OperationExecutionErrorType.CONFIRMATION

        Notes:

        • Multiple instance of OperationExecutionErrorType.ERROR or OperationExecutionErrorType.WARNING can be returned through OperatoinResult. They will be displayed all together in a single message dialog.
        • OperationExecutionErrorType.CONFIRMATION must be the only returned message. Otherwise it will be ignored.
        Transaction type: NON TRANSACTIONAL
        Parameters:
        notAMatchTarget - an object which should not be matched with the recordsToUnmatch.
        recordsToUnmatch - records that should be unmatched from notAMatchTarget.
        Returns:
        OperationResult instance.
        See Also:
        OperationResult

      • afterEverything

        OperationResult afterEverything(BDDObject notAMatchTarget,
                                List<BDDObject> recordsToUnmatch)
        Called when BDD has successfully removed corresponding records from [BO]_MTCH table and successfully committed database transaction. Is suitable for any operations to be performed outside the transaction. This type of operation supports the following return codes:
        • OperationExecutionErrorType.WARNING an informational message at the end of the operation.

        Note:Multiple instance of OperationExecutionErrorType.WARNING can be returned through OperatoinResult. They will be displayed all together in a single message dialog.

        Transaction type:NON TRANSACTIONAL

        Parameters:
        notAMatchTarget - an object which should not be matched with the recordsToUnmatch.
        recordsToUnmatch - records that should be unmatched from notAMatchTarget.
        Returns:
        OperationResult instance.
        See Also:
        OperationResult

      • afterMarkNotAMatch

        OperationResult afterMarkNotAMatch(BDDObject mergeTarget,
                                   List<BDDObject> recordsToMark)
        Called when BDD has successfully removed corresponding records from [BO]_MTCH table but database transaction is not yet committed. Is suitable for post-operation updates. This type of operation supports the following return codes:
        • OperationExecutionErrorType.ERROR

        Note:Multiple instance of OperationExecutionErrorType.ERROR can be returned through OperatoinResult. They will be displayed all together in a single message dialog.

        Transaction type:TRANSACTIONAL

        Parameters:
        mergeTarget - an object which should not be matched with the recordsToUnmatch.
        recordsToMark - records that should be unmatched from notAMatchTarget.
        Returns:
        OperationResult instance.
        See Also:
        OperationResult

      • beforeMarkNotAMatch

        OperationResult beforeMarkNotAMatch(BDDObject mergeTarget,
                                    List<BDDObject> recordsToMark)

        Called when BDD starts to remove records from [BO]_MTCH table. Is suitable for pre-operation updates. This type of operation supports the following return codes:

        • OperationExecutionErrorType.ERROR

        Note:Multiple instance of OperationExecutionErrorType.ERROR can be returned through OperatoinResult. They will be displayed all together in a single message dialog.

        Transaction type:TRANSACTIONAL

        Parameters:
        mergeTarget - an object which should not be matched with the recordsToUnmatch.
        recordsToMark - records that should be unmatched from notAMatchTarget.
        Returns:
        OperationResult instance.

        OperationResult
